2c71bb8e-b8c9-4638-9112-375d38913c9e.content:
The next big thing was Ethereum.

A programmable decentralized accounting system.

This opened a world of opportunities.

It allowed people to start building applications using the blockchain, make it perform anything you can program a computer to do.

This all sounds a bit abstract but here's the huge difference between the applications built on a blockchain & applications built on a centralized database...

With an application built on Ethereum, you can be sure that it does what it says it does because you can read the code that its running.

If you deposit your money in a contract, it wont get loaned

Another huge piece is that all applications built on Ethereum are, at least in theory, interoperable.

Meaning the same data & functionality is available across different interfaces, can be composed into bigger applications or just used across different platforms.

If you want to learn more about why this is significant, go read about programmable blockchains in context.

Get it? Big deal.
